{
  "text": "As previous research has shown, modification of the excitability of the left dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC) and the primary motor cortex (M1) can significantly change behavior associated with these areas [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The aim of this study is to test if anodal, cathodal and sham transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS) in DLPFC and M1 can modulate set shifting tasks. Objectively, we aim to test if the effects of tDCS on performance are due to changes in the speed of processing, shift costs, alterations in irrelevant set filtering or in the number of errors.",
